Sentencas: The microstructural and electrochemical properties of anodes obtained by impregnation of the La0.4Sr0.6Ti0.8Mn0.2O3 +/- d (LSTM) oxide system into two types of anode substrates such as Ni/8YSZ substrate (Ni (E)/8YSZ) and partially Ni removed Ni/8YSZ substrate (Ni(R)/8YSZ) were investigated in order to apply them as anode material for solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: Microstructural and electrochemical properties of impregnated La0.4Sr0.6Ti0.8Mn0.2O3±d into a partially removed Ni SOFC anode substrate

Sentencas: All of the samples with LSTM impregnated on Ni (R)/8YSZ show higher electrical conductivity values than those of unimpregnated Ni (E)/8YSZ under dry H-2 condition.
Titulo: Microstructural and electrochemical properties of impregnated La0.4Sr0.6Ti0.8Mn0.2O3±d into a partially removed Ni SOFC anode substrate

Sentencas: The highest electrical conductivity values of 2041.2, 1877.4, and 1764.3 S/cm at 700, 800 and 900 degrees C can be achieved by samples with 3 wt% impregnated LSTM on Ni (R)/8YSZ.
Titulo: Microstructural and electrochemical properties of impregnated La0.4Sr0.6Ti0.8Mn0.2O3±d into a partially removed Ni SOFC anode substrate

Sentencas: From the XPS analysis, the existence of a Ti metal peak on the surface of LSTM was only measured for the LSTM (3 wt%)-Ni (R)/8YSZ sample, metallic titanium on the surface can improve the electrical catalytic reaction.
Titulo: Microstructural and electrochemical properties of impregnated La0.4Sr0.6Ti0.8Mn0.2O3±d into a partially removed Ni SOFC anode substrate

Sentencas: LSTM (3 wt%)-Ni (R)/8YSZ showed higher electrical conductivity values then those of LSTM (3 wt%)-Ni (E)/8YSZ in all the temperature ranges measured in the case of dry CH 4 supply.
Titulo: Microstructural and electrochemical properties of impregnated La0.4Sr0.6Ti0.8Mn0.2O3±d into a partially removed Ni SOFC anode substrate

Sentencas: Finally, the electrical conductivity of LSTM (3 wt%)-Ni (R)/8YSZ was stably maintained even when exposed to dry CH4 condition at 900 degrees C for a long time (100 h).
Titulo: Microstructural and electrochemical properties of impregnated La0.4Sr0.6Ti0.8Mn0.2O3±d into a partially removed Ni SOFC anode substrate
